# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Units
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------

oakcurric:unit-28
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Geometrical properties: similarity and Pythagoras' theorem"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit explores the concepts of congruence and similarity, and ways to prove or disprove similarity between shapes. We then explore further properties of triangles with Pythagoras' Theorem."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on knowledge developed in work on transformations, angles and properties of triangles. Pupils explored the effects of different transformations and whether the transformed shape was congruent or similar to the original shape. This knowledge is built upon and applied to new contexts as pupils formalise the criteria for determining congruence in triangles and study rotational symmetry. This unit also prepares pupils for learning about trigonometry to extend a right-angled triangle in the unit circle to any other right-angled triangle.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Recognise right-angled triangles
Apply Pythagoras' Theorem to find missing lengths
Use ratios in similar shapes""" ;
  curric:id "28"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.528746Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure .

oakcurric:unit-25
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Perimeter, area and volume"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils extend their knowledge of shapes by exploring the properties of circles and composite shapes before developing understanding of 3-D shapes including surface area and volume."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit is an extension of the perimeter and area unit in year 7 (which focused on polygons), and extends this knowledge to focus on circles and circle based composite shapes then extending to look at the concept of prisms and volume.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Use standard formulas for rectangles and cuboids
Convert between units of measure
Calculate dimensions of composite shapes""" ;
  curric:id "25"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.559435Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure ,
    oakcurric:thread-number .

oakcurric:unit-24
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Numerical summaries of data"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils explore the concept of measures of central tendancy, developing understanding of different types of average and their relative benefits and drawbacks. We then investigate other summaries of data such as the range and data comparison techniques."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Building on work pupils have undertaken on averages in key stage 2, and linking to the previous unit where we summarised data graphically, pupils now explore representing data numerically. Pupils focus on the concept of measures of central tendency and range. We also begin to look at correlation as a relationship between data.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Calculate mean, median, mode and range
Organise data in frequency tables
Interpret results in context""" ;
  curric:id "24"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.559989Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-statistics .

oakcurric:unit-2583
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Maths in the workplace"@en ;
  rdfs:comment "[TO BE ADDED]"@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow "[TO BE ADDED]" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Read tables, charts, and schedules
Perform calculations with money and units
Interpret job-based and practical contexts using maths""" ;
  curric:id "2583"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.560543Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 .

oakcurric:unit-19
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Sequences"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit we develop knowledge of sequences to be able to identify, determine, and continue arithmetic sequences. We finish the unit by looking at how sequences may be reprsented graphically."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit pupils are developing their knowledge of plotting coordinates by exploring the idea that a set of points can satisfy a mathematical relationship. This unit sets the foundation for working with graphical representations of linear equations.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Recognise and continue number patterns
Understand position-to-term rules
Use nth term to generate a sequence""" ;
  curric:id "19"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.572596Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-algebra .

oakcurric:unit-21
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Solving linear equations"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will learn how to find a value that satisfies a linear relationship when one value is known both with a single step operation, and multiple step operations. A variety of cases are explored including using brackets and rearranging."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Further to graphing linear sequences in the previous unit, pupils now learn to connect understanding with solving linear equations after demonstrating how for each point on a linear graph there is a unique solution to the equation of the line.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Understand and apply inverse operations
Simplify algebraic expressions
Solve one-step and two-step equations""" ;
  curric:id "21"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.573148Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-algebra .

oakcurric:unit-34
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Standard form"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils learn to recognise, interpret and write in standard form. Pupils then extend this knowledge so that they can order numbers written in standard form."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds from arithmetic procedures with integers and decimals. In the prior unit, pupils learnt how to factorise multiples of 10 in order to simplify calculations. This understanding is further developed in this unit as values are converted to meet the conditions for standard form.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Understand place value and powers of 10
Convert between standard and ordinary notation
Multiply and divide using powers of 10""" ;
  curric:id "34"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.573670Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number .

oakcurric:unit-33
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Trigonometry"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils learn how to recognise the relationship between the unit circle and the trigonometric ratios of sine, cosine and tangent. Pupils then apply this knowledge to solve trigonometric problems."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils have recently learned about geometrical properties of similarity and the Pythagorean Theorem. This knowledge is further developed to build on their understanding of congruence and similarity with right-angled triangles. In this unit, similarity is used to extend a right-angled triangle in the unit circle to any other right-angled triangle.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Label sides in right-angled triangles (opposite, adjacent, hypotenuse)
Use sine, cosine and tangent ratios
Rearrange and solve trigonometric equations""" ;
  curric:id "33"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.574202Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure ,
    oakcurric:thread-ratio-and-proportion .

oakcurric:unit-15
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Arithmetic procedures with fractions"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits and secures fraction operations and extends pupil understanding to division of whole numbers by fractions and division of fractions by fractions."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit continues from the previous one in deepening pupil understanding of fractions whilst also being explicitly linked to the 'arithmetic procedures with integers and decimals' unit.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Add, subtract, multiply and divide fractions
Simplify fractions and find common denominators
Convert between improper fractions and mixed numbers""" ;
  curric:id "15"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.587213Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number .

oakcurric:unit-14
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Comparing and ordering fractions and decimals (positive and negative)"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit develops understanding and manipulation of fractions, including conversion between fractions to terminating and recurring decimals. Pupils then learn strategies to order fractions of increasing complexity."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds upon work done in the 'arithmetic procedures with integers and decimals' unit, supporting further development of fluency in working with decimals as well as fractions.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Recognise and convert between fractions and decimals
Understand number lines with negative values
Compare values using place value and visual representations""" ;
  curric:id "14"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.587776Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number .

oakcurric:unit-13
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Perimeter and area"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils investigate how to calculate the area and perimeter of rectilinear shapes, and composite shapes using rectangles and triangles. They will also derive simple area formulae."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit requires some confidence in the use of formulae and simple algebra, hence it has been positioned after pupils have done some work on algebraic manipulation and number operations. This unit also prepares pupils for further work on geometry later in the year.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Identify 2D shapes and their properties
Use and apply standard formulas for area and perimeter
Calculate with units of length and area""" ;
  curric:id "13"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.588317Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure .

oakcurric:unit-16
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Understanding multiplicative relationships: fractions and ratio"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces the concept of multiplicative relationsihps, and connects fractions to the idea of ratios. Ratios are then explored in depth and used to solve contextual problems such as those involving exchange rates and general conversions."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit finishes our work with fractions in Year 7, relying upon pupil understanding of multiplication of fractions, and explicitly connecting fractions with ratios and general multiplicative relationships.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Convert between fractions and decimals
Use fractions to represent parts of a whole
Apply ratios to compare and scale quantities""" ;
  curric:id "16"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.593575Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-ratio-and-proportion ,
    oakcurric:thread-number .

oakcurric:unit-8
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Properties of number: factors, multiples, squares and cubes"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils develop their understanding of factors and multiples, then extend this knowledge to learn general divisibility tests for integers and develop strategies to determine the highest common factor and lowest common multiple of two or more integers."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit continues to develop proficiency in handling and recognising different types of numbers, as well as understanding their mathematical structure in order to be more efficient and fluent with mathematical operations in the following unit.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Identify and list factors and multiples
Recognise and calculate square and cube numbers
Apply divisibility rules and prime factorisation""" ;
  curric:id "8"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.594145Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number .

oakcurric:unit-23
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Graphical representations of data"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will interpret and construct a range of representations of data including bar charts, pie charts and scatter graphs."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils have prepared for this unit earlier in the year by looking at graphical representations of sequences. We build upon that knowledge to show that data can be represented in further ways as well as how to construct and interpret those representations.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Draw and interpret bar charts, line graphs and pie charts
Choose appropriate graphs for different types of data
Understand and use frequency and grouped data""" ;
  curric:id "23"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.594677Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-statistics .

oakcurric:unit-26
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Geometrical properties: polygons"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils will investigate internal and external angles of polygons and angles made with a transveral and parallel lines. Pupils will develop their ability to formally prove properties of polygons to generalise."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on knowledge developed investigating angles and continues work done in the previous unit investigating polygons. Here pupils will develop understanding of external and internal angles of polygons and traversals through parallel lines""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Identify and classify polygons by sides and angles
Use angle rules (interior, exterior)
Calculate sum of angles and solve problems using reasoning""" ;
  curric:id "26"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.595218Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure .

oakcurric:unit-11
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Expressions and equations"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn about generalisation and formal algebraic manipulation techniques such as substitution, collecting like terms and factorising."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit is a natural extension of the number work in the previous units. We are now seeking to generalise patterns and behaviours that were first seen in the number units taught before, and pulling in key skills such as factorisation and multiplication of brackets as part of algebraic manipulation.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Simplify algebraic expressions
Solve linear equations and substitute values
Rearrange and manipulate formulas""" ;
  curric:id "11"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.595770Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-algebra .

oakcurric:unit-35
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Graphical representations"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils draw, interpret and utilise linear graphs to solve problems. This knowledge is further extended to look at intersecting graphs."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds knowledge from previous work on non-linear relationships. In that unit, pupils considered geometric sequences and how they might be represented graphically. In this unit, pupils study the graphical representation to link features of the graph to its equation.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Plot points and draw axes
Interpret bar charts, line graphs, and scatter graphs
Select appropriate graphs for different types of data""" ;
  curric:id "35"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.611027Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-algebra .

oakcurric:unit-10
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Place value"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils revisit, secure and develop their understanding of place value with integers, decimals, fractions, metric and imperial units. This knowledge is then extended to order and compare numbers of increasing complexity."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """We begin year 7 with checking, securing and further development of place value in order to prepare adequately for further work on number in the following units for this term.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Understand value of digits in large and decimal numbers
Multiply and divide by powers of 10
Convert between standard and decimal forms""" ;
  curric:id "10"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.611561Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number .

oakcurric:unit-29
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Probability: possible outcomes"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces and explores the concept of liklihood as a relative measure, and demonstrates multiple ways to represent likelihood such as Venn diagrams, tree diagrams and two-way tables."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit is the first introduction to probability and likelihood. Pupils develop their understanding of how likely something is, looking at relative likelihoods and displaying outcomes but without  formalising probability using measurable numerical values at this stage. Pupils explore different ways to display outcomes to gain a sense of what it means to say something is likely or unlikely in preparation for more calculative methods and theoretical probability in the next unit.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Understand outcomes and sample spaces
Use fractions and percentages to represent probability
Recognise equally likely events and basic probability rules""" ;
  curric:id "29"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.612093Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-probability .

oakcurric:unit-30
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Probability: theoretical probabilities"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit we build upon the concept of likelihood to work more mathematically with more measurable probability using fraction and decimal representations to both interpret and calculate. We revisit and develop ways to represent and compare probabilities."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Further to developing the basic ideas and foundations of probability, we move towards more abstract measures of likelihood using calculations to assign numerical values to probability. We then revisit the visual models of probability established in the previous unit through the lens of representing and utilising theoretical probability.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Define probability as a ratio between favourable and possible outcomes
Represent events using lists, tables or diagrams
Calculate probabilities of single and combined events""" ;
  curric:id "30"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.612621Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-probability .

oakcurric:unit-12
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Plotting coordinates"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils revisit and further develop their understanding of the coordinate plane, and learn how to plot non-integer coordinates. Pupils then plot from an equation both by hand and by using technology."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Continuing from their recent work using algebra, this unit introduces plotting from algebraic equations and developing generalisations from a set of coordinate pairs.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Understand and use axes in all four quadrants
Plot and read coordinates accurately
Recognise and describe geometric figures using coordinates""" ;
  curric:id "12"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.620909Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-algebra .

oakcurric:unit-2584
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Thinking critically with maths"@en ;
  rdfs:comment "[TO BE ADDED]"@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow "[TO BE ADDED]" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Interpret and evaluate information logically
Justify reasoning using numerical and graphical evidence
Identify assumptions and question validity of arguments""" ;
  curric:id "2584"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.623193Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 .

oakcurric:unit-9
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Arithmetic procedures with integers and decimals"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils develop their ability and efficacy with the four operations including more complicated and challenging calculations involving fractions, decimals and negative numbers. This leads into an exploration of the priority order of operations."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on knowledge established in work on factors, multiples squares and cubes, building on the understanding that any positive integer can be expressed as a product of its factors. This skill is used here to explore multiplying and dividing with decimals.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Perform all four operations with whole numbers
Add, subtract, multiply and divide decimals
Apply integer rules (positive/negative) to calculations""" ;
  curric:id "9"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.623744Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number .

oakcurric:unit-20
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Graphical representations of linear equations"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unti we develop understanding of linear relationships and explore the key features of a linear equation such as the gradient, intercept and determining an equation from coordinate pairs."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit we continue to build on knowledge developed in the previous work on sequences and build confidence in how a linear sequence produces a linear relationship. We represent that graphically along with development of understanding of the equation of a line, positive, negative relationships and the idea that a linear sequence can produce an infinite set of points.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Rearrange equations into y = mx + c form
Use tables of values to plot lines
Identify features of straight-line graphs""" ;
  curric:id "20"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.629964Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-algebra .

oakcurric:unit-31
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Non-linear relationships"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit we explore geometric and special number sequences like the Fibonacci sequence. We develop strategies to recognise types of sequence and continue them."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds from the sequences unit in Year 8. We develop understanding of sequences further to look at geometric and other non-linear sequences and how they appear graphically.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Recognise non-linear patterns in graphs and tables
Understand simple quadratic and exponential relationships
Plot and interpret curves on coordinate grids""" ;
  curric:id "31"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.636145Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-algebra .

oakcurric:unit-27
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Constructions"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit we develop skills in using a pair of compasses and ruler to construct various accurate shapes and angles including triangles, rhombi, perpendicular lines and angle bisectors."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """After studying polygons and circles in depth in previous units, this year culminates in learning to mathematically construct these shapes using knowledge of the properties of triangles, quadrilaterals and circles in order to draw them accurately.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Use ruler and compass for straight-edge and arcs
Construct perpendiculars and bisectors
Interpret geometric conditions in drawings""" ;
  curric:id "27"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.646590Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure .

oakcurric:unit-22
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Understanding multiplicative relationships: percentages and proportionality"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils explore multiplicative relationships with percentages, direct and inverse proportion."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils build upon key stage 2 work with finding percentages of amounts, then extending their knowledge to percentage change, connecting to previous learning around decimals and fractions. Pupils then explore a more general exploration of multiplicative relationships.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Convert between fractions, decimals, and percentages
Understand ratio and scaling
Solve problems involving direct proportion""" ;
  curric:id "22"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.647405Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-ratio-and-proportion ,
    oakcurric:thread-number .

oakcurric:unit-17
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Transformations"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces pupils to shape tranformations: enlargements, rotations, reflections and translations both by hand and with technology."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit utilises prior knowledge with ratios and percentages, applying general multiplicative relationships to the transformation of shapes, whilst also drawing upon recently developed knowledge of the coordinate plane.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Identify and describe reflections, rotations, translations and enlargements
Plot points and shapes in all four quadrants
Use coordinates to represent movements""" ;
  curric:id "17"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.651726Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-geometry-and-measure .

oakcurric:unit-18
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Estimation and rounding"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit helps pupils understand rounding to different decimal places, and significant figures. Pupils will also learn how to truncate numbers and understand the contexts in which these skills are useful. The unit ends will an exploration of rounding and inequality errors."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Students up to this point have been working with integer values and have had few opportunities to work explicitly on estimation. We are starting the year with something that is familiar for students and extend knowledge of estimation and rounding to include more work on rounding with decimals and significant figures.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Round numbers to nearest 10, 100, 1000
Round decimals to 1 or 2 decimal places
Estimate calculations using compatible numbers""" ;
  curric:id "18"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.652812Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-number .

oakcurric:unit-2582
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Maths and the environment"@en ;
  rdfs:comment "[TO BE ADDED]"@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow "[TO BE ADDED]" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Interpret real-world contexts using mathematical reasoning
Use units and conversions appropriately
Read and represent data using graphs and tables""" ;
  curric:id "2582"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.661368Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 .

oakcurric:unit-3777
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Calculator functionality"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit teaches how to use scientific calculators and expores their functionality"""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """It is important to dedicate some time to understanding the functionality of modern scientific calculators so that they can be used appropriately.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Perform basic operations accurately
Use brackets, powers, roots and memory functions
Interpret calculator display and rounding appropriately""" ;
  curric:id "3777"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.662913Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 .

oakcurric:unit-32
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Expressions and formulae"@en ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit develops pupil understanding of formulae and how to rearrange them. Pupils will learn how to recognise and manipulate binomials and learn to recognise the difference of two squares."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on solving linear equations from year 7 where pupils learnt to rearrange aan equation to find a specific value that satisfied the equation. In expressions and formulae, pupils use their understanding of rearrangement to change the subject of a formula. Pupils are then introduced binomial equations in preparation for trigonometry.""" ;
  curric:unitPriorKnowledgeRequirements """Simplify algebraic expressions
Use substitution in expressions and formulas
Rearrange formulas involving one or more steps""" ;
  curric:id "32"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-02-12T08:59:07.663981Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf natcurric:scheme-mathematics-key-stage-3 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-algebra .

